4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT PROVIDING FOR PRIVACY IN CERTAIN RESTROOMS,
5 CHANGING ROOMS, AND SLEEPING QUARTERS; REQUIRING THAT COVERED ENTITIES DESIGNATE
6 MULTI-OCCUPANCY RESTROOMS, CHANGING ROOMS, AND SLEEPING QUARTERS FOR THE
7 EXCLUSIVE USE OF MALES OR FEMALES; REQUIRING THAT INDIVIDUALS USE RESTROOMS,
8 CHANGING ROOMS, AND SLEEPING QUARTERS DESIGNATED FOR THEIR SEX; PROVIDING
9 DEFINITIONS; PROVIDING EXCEPTIONS; PROVIDING REMEDIES; AND PROVIDING AN IMMEDIATE
10 EFFECTIVE DATE.”
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
13
14 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Purpose. The purposes of [sections 1 through 4] are to:
15 (1) reaffirm the longstanding meanings of the terms "sex", "male", and "female" in law; and
16 (2) preserve women's restrooms, changing rooms, and sleeping quarters for women in facilities
17 where women have traditionally been afforded privacy and safety from acts of abuse, harassment, sexual
18 assault, and violence committed by men.
19
20 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Definitions. For the purposes of [sections 1 through 4], the following
21 definitions apply:
22 (1) "Changing room" means a room or area in which an individual may be in a state of undress in
23 the presence of others, including a locker room or shower room.
24 (2) "Correctional center" means a facility that houses individuals charged with or convicted of a
25 criminal offense and that is designed, constructed, or operated by the department of corrections.
26 (3) "Covered entity" means a correctional center, a juvenile detention facility, a local domestic
27 violence program, a public building, or a public school.
28 (4) "Female" means a member of the human species who, under normal development, has XX
