9 401.
10 (7) "Male" means a member of the human species who, under normal development, has XY
11 chromosomes and produces or would produce small, mobile gametes, or sperm, during his life cycle and has a
12 reproductive and endocrine system oriented around the production of those gametes. An individual who would
13 otherwise fall within this definition, but for a biological or genetic condition, is male.
14 (8) "Multi-occupancy" means a space that is designed for use by multiple individuals
15 simultaneously.
16 (9) "Public building" means a building that is owned or leased by a public agency as defined in 18-
17 1-101 and that is open to the public, including but not limited to:
18 (a) a building that is used for educational, office, or institutional purposes; or
19 (b) a library, museum, school, hospital, auditorium, dormitory, or university building.
20 (10) "Public school" means a noncharter public school or a public charter school as those terms are
21 defined in 20-6-803.
22 (11) "Restroom" means a room that includes one or more toilets or urinals.
23 (12) "Sex" means the organization of the body parts and gametes for reproduction in human beings
24 and other organisms. In human beings, there are exactly two sexes, male and female, with two corresponding
25 types of gametes. The sexes are determined by the biological and genetic indication of male or female,
26 including sex chromosomes, naturally occurring sex chromosomes, gonads, and nonambiguous internal and
27 external genitalia present at birth, without regard to an individual's psychological, behavioral, social, chosen, or
28 subjective experience of gender.
