4 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Safety and privacy in covered entities. (1) A covered entity shall
5 designate each multi-occupancy restroom, changing room, or sleeping quarters for the exclusive use of females
6 or males.
7 (2) A restroom, changing room, or sleeping quarters within a covered entity that is designated for
8 females or males may be used only by members of that sex. Except as provided in subsection (4), an individual
9 may not enter a restroom, changing room, or sleeping quarters that is designated for females or males unless
10 the individual is a member of the designated sex.
11 (3) A covered entity shall take reasonable steps to provide individuals with privacy from members
12 of the opposite sex in designated restrooms, changing rooms, and sleeping quarters.
13 (4) This section does not apply to an individual who enters a restroom, changing room, or sleeping
14 quarters designated for the opposite sex:
15 (a) to perform custodial services or maintenance;
16 (b) to render medical assistance;
17 (c) to render law enforcement assistance; or
18 (d) to provide services or render aid during a natural disaster or declared emergency or if
19 necessary to prevent a serious threat to good order and safety.
20 (5) (a) For any activity or event authorized by a public school during which students share sleeping
21 quarters, a student may not be required to share sleeping quarters with a member of the opposite sex unless
22 the other individual is a member of the student's family, such as a parent, guardian, sibling, or grandparent.
23 (b) In any other facility or setting in a public school where an individual may be in a state of
24 undress in the presence of others, school personnel shall provide separate, private areas designated for use by
25 individuals based on their sex. Except as provided in subsection (4), an individual may not enter a private area
26 unless the individual is a member of the designated sex.
27 (6) This section may not be construed to prohibit a covered entity from:
28 (a) adopting policies necessary to accommodate individuals protected under the Americans with
