4 (c) redesignating a multi-occupancy restroom, changing room, or sleeping quarters designated for
5 exclusive use by one sex to a designation for exclusive use by the opposite sex.
6
7 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Remedies. (1) An individual who, while accessing a restroom or
8 changing room designated for use by the individual's sex, encounters another individual of the opposite sex in
9 the restroom or changing room has a private cause of action for declaratory and injunctive relief, nominal
10 damages, and any other appropriate relief against the covered entity that:
11 (a) provided the other individual permission to use a restroom or changing room designated for the
12 opposite sex; or
13 (b) failed to take reasonable steps to prohibit the other individual from using the restroom or
14 changing room designated for the opposite sex.
15 (2) An individual who is required by a covered entity to share sleeping quarters with an individual
16 of the opposite sex has a private cause of action for declaratory and injunctive relief, nominal damages, and
17 any other appropriate relief against the covered entity.
18 (3) (a) All civil actions brought pursuant to this section must be initiated within 2 years after the
19 violation occurred.
20 (b) An individual aggrieved under this section who prevails in court may recover reasonable
21 attorney fees and costs from the offending covered entity.
22
23 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Codification instruction. [Sections 1 through 4] are intended to be
24 codified as a new part in Title 50, chapter 4, and the provisions of Title 50, chapter 4, apply to [sections 1
25 through 4].
26
